data.text:
Tournai Cathedral, Tournai, Belgium

Latitude and longitude coordinates are: 50.606491, 3.388880.

Tournai Cathedral is a large historic church located at Place de l'Evêché 1, in the very center of Tournai city in Belgium. Built in the late 12th century, it is one of the largest and the tallest churches in the country, which has been continuously renovated and reconstructed during its historical period. The cathedral is an example of an old Gothic architecture, with tall bell towers and large pilasters. A traditional large nave can be observed inside of the church.
